Luminoveau — VirtualControls touch improvements (additive, opt-in)
===================================================================

These changes came out of a DOOM port and are all backward-compatible: new
methods and members with defaults that preserve the current behaviour (nothing
changes unless a caller opts in). Files touched:

    src/platform/input/virtualcontrols.h
    src/platform/input/virtualcontrols.cpp

What's added
------------
1. Physical-pixel mode — SetUsePhysicalCoords(bool).
   VirtualControls rendered and hit-tested in logical pixels (Window::GetWidth/
   Height). An app that draws its 2D scene in physical pixels (swapchain-sized
   canvas on a HiDPI display) got the controls stuck in the logical top-left
   quadrant. viewW()/viewH() now switch to physical when enabled. Default off →
   unchanged.

2. Look region — SetLookRegionEnabled(bool), ConsumeLookDelta(), ConsumeLookTap(),
   IsLookActive(). A drag in the right half (outside buttons/joystick) accumulates
   a per-frame delta (a second stick for camera turn/pitch); a barely-moved
   press+release is reported as a tap (tap-to-fire vs drag-to-look). Multi-touch:
   left joystick, right look, buttons on top. Mouse-driven too, for desktop testing.

3. Button labels — SetButtonLabel(int, string). Centered text on a button
   (default font), auto-scaled to fit. VirtualButton gains a std::string label.

4. Viewport-relative sizing — SetControlScaleToViewport(fraction) and
   SetControlScale(multiplier). cm()-based sizing depends on the reported display
   scale, which mobile Safari/WebGPU reports as a huge value, making the controls
   cover the screen. Viewport-relative sizes the joystick radius to
   fraction*min(viewW,viewH) and derives the rest from the cm ratios (display
   scale cancels out), recomputed on rotation/resize.

5. Mouse-emulation toggle — SetMouseEmulationEnabled(bool). On a real touch device
   the browser also emits synthetic mouse events mirroring each finger; disable
   this so VirtualControls stops reading the mouse. Default on → unchanged.

To apply (from the engine repo root):
    git apply luminoveau-virtualcontrols-touch.patch      # or: patch -p1 < ...

Questions / happy to adjust naming or split into smaller commits if you prefer.

